@startuml State Machine Template
' State Machine Diagram Template
' Author: [Your Name]
' Date: [Date]
' Description: Template for documenting state machines and workflows

!theme materia
title State Machine - [Entity/Process Name]

' Define states with internal behaviors
state "Draft" as draft {
    draft : entry / initializeDocument()
    draft : do / autosave()
    draft : exit / validateMinimumData()
    --
    [*] --> Editing
    Editing --> Editing : modificationsDetected
}

state "Under Review" as review {
    review : entry / notifyReviewers()
    review : do / trackReviewTime()
    review : exit / closeReviewSession()
    --
    [*] --> AwaitingReview
    AwaitingReview --> InReview : reviewerAssigned
    InReview --> AwaitingApproval : reviewCompleted
    AwaitingApproval --> [*]
}

state "Published" as published {
    published : entry / publishToProduction()
    published : do / trackViews()
    --
    [*] --> Live
    state "Live" as live
    state "Unpublished" as unpublished
    
    live --> unpublished : unpublish
    unpublished --> live : republish
}

state "Archived" as archived {
    archived : entry / moveToArchive()
    archived : do / compressData()
}

' Fork and join for parallel processing
state fork_state <<fork>>
state join_state <<join>>

state "Parallel Processing" as parallel {
    [*] --> fork_state
    fork_state --> ValidationCheck
    fork_state --> SecurityScan
    fork_state --> QualityAssurance
    
    ValidationCheck --> join_state
    SecurityScan --> join_state
    QualityAssurance --> join_state
    
    join_state --> [*]
}

' Initial and final states
[*] --> draft : create

' Transitions with guards and actions
draft --> review : submit\n[isComplete && hasContent]\n/ notifyReviewers()
review --> draft : requestChanges\n[reviewerFeedback]\n/ createActionItems()
review --> parallel : approve\n[allReviewersApproved]
parallel --> published : allChecksPassed\n/ generateVersion()

' Conditional transitions
published --> archived : archive\n[daysInactive > 90]\n/ notifyOwner()
published --> draft : unpublishAndEdit\n/ createNewDraft()

' Self-transitions
draft --> draft : autoSave\n[every 30 seconds]
published --> published : updateMetadata\n/ refreshTimestamp()

' Error handling
draft --> [*] : delete\n/ confirmDeletion()
review --> [*] : reject\n[criticalIssues]\n/ notifyAuthor()

' Transition to archive
archived --> [*] : permanentDelete\n[after 1 year]\n/ secureWipe()

' Choice pseudo-state
state choice_state <<choice>>
review --> choice_state
choice_state --> published : [minorChanges]
choice_state --> draft : [majorChanges]

' History pseudo-state (remember last sub-state)
state review {
    state deep_history <<history,type=deep>>
}

' Notes for documentation
note right of draft
  **Draft State**
  - Document can be freely edited
  - Auto-save enabled
  - No version control yet
  - Owner: Document creator
  
  **Entry Conditions:**
  - User must be authenticated
  - Project must be active
end note

note right of review
  **Review Process**
  - Minimum 2 reviewers required
  - 48-hour review SLA
  - Comments tracked in audit log
  - Email notifications sent
  
  **Possible Outcomes:**
  - Approve (requires all reviewers)
  - Request Changes
  - Reject (requires reason)
end note

note right of parallel
  **Automated Checks**
  Runs in parallel:
  1. **Validation Check**
     - Schema validation
     - Required fields
     - Data integrity
  
  2. **Security Scan**
     - Sensitive data detection
     - Access control check
     - Compliance verification
  
  3. **QA**
     - Link validation
     - Asset availability
     - Performance test
end note

note bottom of published
  **Published State**
  - Publicly accessible
  - Version controlled
  - Immutable (create new version to edit)
  - Analytics tracked
  - Can be unpublished temporarily
end note

note left of archived
  **Archive Policy**
  - Auto-archive after 90 days inactive
  - Compressed storage
  - Read-only access
  - Permanent deletion after 1 year
  - Can be restored within 30 days
end note

' State machine metadata
note as MetadataNI
  **Transition Guards:**
  [isComplete] - All required fields filled
  [hasContent] - Minimum content length met
  [allReviewersApproved] - Unanimous approval
  [criticalIssues] - P0/P1 issues found
  [daysInactive > 90] - No activity for 90+ days
  
  **Actions:**
  notifyReviewers() - Send email to review team
  createActionItems() - Generate tasks from feedback
  generateVersion() - Create immutable version
  confirmDeletion() - Require user confirmation
  compressData() - Reduce storage footprint
end note

' Concurrent states
note as ConcurrentNote
  **Concurrent Activities:**
  While in certain states, the system
  maintains concurrent operations:
  - User activity tracking
  - Search index updates
  - Backup synchronization
  - Audit logging
end note

legend right
  |= **Legend** |
  | State | Description |
  | <<fork>> | Fork pseudo-state |
  | <<join>> | Join pseudo-state |
  | <<choice>> | Decision point |
  | <<history>> | Remember last state |
  | [guard] | Transition condition |
  | / action | Transition action |
  | entry / | Action on state entry |
  | do / | Ongoing activity |
  | exit / | Action on state exit |
  
  **Transition Syntax:**
  event [guard] / action
endlegend

footer
  State Machine v1.0
  Last Updated: [Date]
  Implementation: [Spring State Machine / Stateless / Custom]
end footer

@enduml
